
Overview of noun scare

The noun scare has 2 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                        
1. panic, scare -- (sudden mass fear and anxiety over anticipated events; "panic in the stock market"; "a war scare"; "a bomb scare led them to evacuate the building")
2. scare, panic attack -- (a sudden attack of fear)

Overview of verb scare

The verb scare has 2 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (4) frighten, fright, scare, affright -- (cause fear in; "The stranger who hangs around the building frightens me"; "Ghosts could never affright her")
